@spec intervals_spec  src=tests/specs/intervals_spec.lua  loc=128  sha=e33b768  cases=11
@exercises intervals (intervals)
@surface   intervals.seed, intervals.merge, intervals.intersects, intervals.absorbSeeds

# Intent
  intervals is the pure dirt-interval algebra (design/interval-dirt.md).
  A set is `true` (whole channel) or a ppq-ascending, non-overlapping
  list of { loPpq, hiPpq, loUuid, hiUuid }. seed normalises; merge
  coalesces edge-inclusive and collapses to `true` past the cap;
  intersects is edge-inclusive; absorbSeeds folds one flush's seeds into
  the dirt set.

# Cases
  @case 'seed normalises reversed bounds, swapping uuids with them'  [pure]  @ 15-20
  @case 'seed keeps a point interval degenerate'  [pure]  @ 24-28
  @case 'merge passes true through and leaves a singleton alone'  [pure]  @ 34-39
  @case 'merge coalesces overlapping and edge-touching intervals, keeping outer uuids'  [pure]  @ 43-55
  @case 'merge sorts before coalescing and does not mutate its input order'  [pure]  @ 59-65
  @case 'merge subsumes a fully-contained interval without extending the outer hi'  [pure]  @ 69-73
  @case 'merge collapses to true past the size cap'  [pure]  @ 77-82
  @case 'intersects is edge-inclusive and short-circuits on true'  [pure]  @ 88-94
  @case 'absorbSeeds narrows a seeded chan to its merged intervals'  [pure]  @ 100-107
  @case 'absorbSeeds folds an unseeded payload chan whole'  [pure]  @ 111-117
  @case 'absorbSeeds narrows a seeded chan even absent from the payload, overriding a prior true'  [pure]  @ 121-126

# Uses (outbound edges)
  @use call intervals.seed  @ 17,26,37,46,47,48,61,71,80,90,103,114,124
  @use call intervals.merge  @ 36,38,50,62,81
